# === The Tower — Environment Variables ===
#
# FASTEST SETUP: in Terminal, go to this project folder and run:
#   npm run env:init
# That creates .env.local for you (only if it doesn't exist yet).
# Then open .env.local and paste keys after each = sign.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FOR ABSOLUTE BEGINNERS — WHAT IS THIS?
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Your app needs secret passwords ("keys") to talk to Supabase and the AI.
# Those secrets live ONLY in a file named:  .env.local
# This file (.env.example) is the TEMPLATE. It has no real secrets. Safe for GitHub.
# .env.local has YOUR real secrets. Never upload .env.local anywhere.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP-BY-STEP — CREATE .env.local (pick ONE way)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# WAY A — Using the mouse (Finder on Mac)
#   1. In Cursor’s left sidebar, find this file:  .env.example
#   2. Right-click it → Copy
#   3. Right-click empty space in the same folder → Paste Item
#   4. Rename the NEW copy from "copy of .env.example" to exactly:  .env.local
#      (starts with a dot, no .txt at the end)
#
# WAY B — Using the terminal (project folder = where package.json lives)
#   Run:   cp .env.example .env.local
#   Then open .env.local in Cursor and edit it.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP-BY-STEP — FILL IN THE BLANKS (after each "=" sign)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# You will see lines like:   SOME_NAME=
# Put your value RIGHT after the "=" with NO space. Example:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://abcdefgh.supabase.co
#
# DO THESE FIRST (minimum to run the app + AI):
#
#   (1) SUPABASE — website: https://supabase.com
#       - Log in → click YOUR project (The Tower / internship project).
#       - Left sidebar: click the GEAR icon = "Project Settings".
#       - Click "API" in the settings menu.
#         • "Project URL" → copy → paste into NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
#         • "anon" / "public" key (long text) → paste into NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
#         • "service_role" key (long text, SECRET) → paste into SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
#       - Still Project Settings: click "Database".
#         • Find "Connection string" → choose "URI" → copy → paste into SUPABASE_DB_URL=
#         • If it shows [YOUR-PASSWORD], replace that placeholder with your actual DB password
#           (the one you set when you created the Supabase project).
#
#   (2) ANTHROPIC (AI) — website: https://console.anthropic.com
#       - Sign in → Settings or API keys → Create key → copy → ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
#
# OPTIONAL FOR LATER (skip until you need Google login):
#   GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=   and   GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
#   (These come from Google Cloud Console and must match Supabase Auth settings.)
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WHEN YOU ARE DONE
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# - Save .env.local (Cmd+S).
# - In terminal, from this project folder:  npm run dev
# - If the site opens and login works, you did it right.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CHEAT SHEET — WHAT EACH VARIABLE MEANS (PLAIN ENGLISH)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL        = Address of your Supabase project on the internet.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY = Safe "public" key for the browser (still not for GitHub abuse — keep repo private if you can).
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY       = Master key for background jobs ONLY. Never use in browser code.
# SUPABASE_DB_URL                 = Direct line to Postgres for migrations / Drizzle tools.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY               = Pays for / authorizes the Claude AI used in the app.
# GOOGLE_*                        = Only if you use "Sign in with Google" through Supabase.
#
# NEVER commit .env.local (only this .env.example with empty values is safe in git).

# --- Phase 0: Foundation ---

# Supabase (Database + Auth)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
SUPABASE_DB_URL=

# Google OAuth (via Supabase Auth)
# Configure in Google Cloud Console > Credentials > OAuth 2.0 Client ID
# Redirect URI: https://your-project.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# --- Phase 1: Agents ---

# Anthropic (AI SDK provider)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- Phase 2: Background Jobs + Email ---

# Inngest (background job orchestration)
INNGEST_EVENT_KEY=
INNGEST_SIGNING_KEY=

# Resend (outreach email delivery)
RESEND_API_KEY=

# --- Phase 6: Monetization + Polish ---

# Stripe (subscriptions)
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# Upstash Redis (optional but recommended in production — rate-limits /api/cro)
# If empty, CRO chat is not rate-limited (fine for local dev).
# Create free DB: https://upstash.com → copy REST URL + REST TOKEN here.
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=

# OpenWeatherMap (weather-reactive skyline, optional)
OPENWEATHER_API_KEY=
